Just to keep you informed regarding our school attendance policy, the school does not encourage students to miss lessons during term time as we believe in the importance of being in school daily for effective learning. Hence, students must exercise responsibility and work closely with a buddy to be on task with what they might have missed. The student must also take initiative to consult subject teachers to clarify doubts he/she may have. For such cases, student's absenteeism will be considered 'absence without valid reason' and will be given zero marks if there are to be any quizzes or tests conducted during his/her period of absence.

I thank you for working closely with the school to ensure that your child aspires and achieves her best.

You were identified as a close contact of a probable or confirmed COVID case on 22/Jul/2021 at 21:45 by TraceTogether / BluePass. You are issued this Quarantine Order (QO) under the Infectious Diseases Act (IDA) from 26/Jul/2021 to 05/Aug/2021. Your QO will end at 12pm on 05/Aug/2021 or when you receive a negative PCR test result, whichever is later on that day. The QO agent (Certis) will contact you with more information, including transfer arrangements.

What you must do next:
1. Return and stay home immediately
2. Wear a mask and keep a safe distance from others at home
3. Inform close contacts to stay at home and monitor their health until your first swab is negative. They should consult a doctor if unwell
4. Pack a bag (if not quarantined at home)
5. Download Homer app to report health status and location (https://homer.gov.sg/instructions)

You must comply with QO conditions (https://go.gov.sg/qo-annex) and undergo medical examinations, submit blood or other samples and treatment, if required. Non-compliance is a serious offence under the IDA, carrying a fine up to $10,000 and/or up to 6 monthsâ€™ jail.

This QO supersedes any Isolation Order or QO previously issued to you, with immediate effect.

For questions on your QO, please call Certis (63805072) or refer to https://go.gov.sg/faq-loa-shn-qo. If you feel anxious, please call the helplines (https://go.gov.sg/helplines) for emotional support.

Thank you for helping to keep the nation safe.

[19/2/24, 4:53:49â€¯PM] Sinclair: Dear Sir/Madam,

I am writing to express my profound dissatisfaction with the substandard service I received from Citibank's limousine service, which was booked for my recent airport transfers. This letter outlines two separate incidents that not only caused significant inconvenience but also demonstrated a lack of professionalism and customer care that I did not expect from a reputable institution like Citibank.

Incident on Departure:
I had scheduled a pick-up for 7:30 AM (please verify the exact time from your records), but due to an unforeseen flight delay of 2 hours, the service was no longer required at the scheduled time. Despite this common scenario, the driver arrived at the predetermined time without verifying the flight's status, which could have easily been checked to prevent any inconvenience. Upon informing the driver of the cancellation due to the delay, I was taken aback to learn about a $10 cancellation fee imposed by your service. It is unreasonable to penalize customers for circumstances beyond their control, especially when due diligence on the part of the service provider could have averted the situation.

Incident on Arrival:
The return flight was delayed, changing the arrival time from 2340 hrs to 0225 hrs. Despite informing your team of the delay, the coordination and communication were grossly mishandled. A driver messaged to announce his arrival without checking the updated flight details. When my secretary called to rectify the situation, she was met with unprofessionalism and rudeness by a staff member named Ali. His refusal to acknowledge the absence of an SMS notification regarding the limousine details, insistence on mistrusting my secretary's words, and his overall demeanor were far from the standard of service expected from Citibank. Furthermore, the eventual resolution was delayed and incomplete, lacking crucial details previously provided like the car's license plate number.

Such experiences not only caused unnecessary stress and inconvenience but also reflected poorly on Citibank's commitment to customer service excellence. It is distressing that the basic principles of service, such as verifying flight details for airport pickups and transparent communication, were overlooked. Moreover, the confrontational attitude of your staff member, Ali, exacerbated the situation, making it even more unpleasant.

I urge you to address these issues promptly. I expect a thorough investigation into these incidents, a formal apology for the inconvenience caused, and a waiver of the unjust cancellation fee. Moreover, I would appreciate a response from a manager regarding the steps Citibank will take to prevent such occurrences in the future and to ensure that all staff members are adequately trained in customer service etiquette.

Thank you for your attention to this matter. I look forward to your prompt response.

[19/2/24, 6:34:53â€¯PM] Sinclair: Dear Sir/Madam,

I am writing to express my deep dissatisfaction with the poor standard of service provided by Citibank's limousine service, which was booked for airport transfers. The series of events that unfolded not only caused inconvenience but also highlighted a serious lack of professionalism and customer care.

Incident on Departure:
The limousine was scheduled for a 7:30 AM pickup. However, due to an unexpected flight delay of 2 hours, the service was no longer required at the original time. Despite this, the driver arrived without verifying the flight's updated schedule, a basic precaution that should have been taken. When I informed the driver of the cancellation, I was informed about a $10 cancellation fee, which seems unfair under the circumstances, especially since the delay was easily verifiable.

Incident on Arrival:
My return flight was delayed, changing my expected arrival from 2340 hrs to 0225 hrs. Despite this, I received a message from the driver at 0016 hrs stating he was on site. When my secretary called to address the delay, she encountered significant unprofessionalism from a staff member named Ali. Not only did Ali refuse to acknowledge the lack of communication (no SMS regarding the limousine details was received), but he also initially refused to provide his name, questioning why it was necessary. This behavior is unacceptable and not indicative of the service standards expected from Citibank.

The situation from start to finish, from 0016 hrs to 0126 hrs, took an hour and ten minutes to resolve, during which no satisfactory solution was provided promptly. Furthermore, the limousine provided for the airport pickup did not include a child seat as requested and for which I was already charged, adding to the inconvenience and distress caused by this entire experience.

The lack of basic service elements such as verifying flight details for airport pickups, the absence of essential amenities like a child seat, and the poor communication and customer service, particularly from Ali, are alarming. It reflects poorly on Citibank's commitment to customer satisfaction and service excellence.

I request a full investigation into these incidents, an apology for the inconvenience and distress caused, a refund of the unjust cancellation fee, and a refund for the unprovided child seat. Additionally, I insist on a response from a manager regarding how Citibank intends to prevent such failures in the future and ensure all staff members are trained to treat customers with the respect and professionalism they deserve.

Thank you for your immediate attention to this matter. I look forward to your prompt and satisfactory resolution.
